grumman ranks no  on the  fortune  list of americas largest corporations and ranks in the top ten militaryfriendly employers it is headquartered in west falls church virginia contents  business sectors  aerospace systems  mission systems  technical services  affiliated companies and partners  history  s  s   to present  corporate governance  corporate headquarters  accolades and criticism  environmental record  political contributions and governmental ties  controversies  international traffic in arms regulations itar violations  see also  references  notes  bibliography  external links business sectorsedit northrop grumman is made up of three business sectors aerospace systems mission systems and technology services aerospace systemsedit northrop grumman manufactured the b spirit strategic bomber a bqm chukar unmanned aerial drone launches from a us navy vessel aerospace systems headquartered in redondo beach california produces aircraft spacecraft highenergy laser systems and microelectronics for the us and other nations this includes surveillance and reconnaissance protected communications intelligence battle management strike operations electronic warfare and missile defense to earth observation space science and space exploration the b spirit strategic bomber the ec joint stars surveillance aircraft the rq global hawk and the t talon supersonic trainer are used by the us air force the us army uses northrop grummans rq hunter unmanned air vehicle which has been in operational use since  the us navy uses northrop grummanbuilt aerial vehicles such as the bqm chukar rq global hawk based bams uas grumman c greyhound grumman e hawkeye and the eab prowler northrop grumman provides major components and assemblies for different aircraft such as fa hornet faef super hornet and the eag growler mission systemsedit northrop grumman mission systems headquartered in linthicum maryland creates military radar sensors and related products including ci radar systems for air defense airspace management radar systems such as amass and battlefield surveillance systems like the airborne reconnaissance low arl tactical aircraft sensors include the anapg radar the anapg advanced agile beam fire control radar advanced electronically scanned array aesa and the scalable agile beam radar sabr aesa upgrade for the f fighting falcon the anapg aesa radar for the f raptor and the anapg aesa radar for the f lightning ii and the anaaq electrooptical distributed aperture system das for the f and the apq passive electronically scanned array pesa radar for the b lancercitation needed electronic systems produces and maintains the awacs aerial surveillance systems for the us the united kingdom nato japan and others northrop grumman is the prime contractor for the development and integration of the air forces billion multiplatform radar technology insertion program northrop grumman also supports the us ballistic missile program integrates various command control and intelligence systems and provides technical and management services to governmental and military customers all with an emphasis on cyber security many other smaller products are made by northrop grumman such as night vision goggles and secure communications equipmentcitation needed technical servicesedit the technical services sector headquartered in mcnair virginia with a herndon mailing address works on logistics solutions from modernization and sustainment to supply chain management training and simulation and automated test equipment vinnell a technical services northrop grumman subsidiary provides training and communications for the military in  it landed a  million contract to train the iraqi army in  the company won a  billion contract with virginia to overhaul most of the states it operations later that year the united kingdom paid  billion in a contract with the company to provide maintenance of the countrys defensive radar northrop grumman performs various functions in the war on drugs the company sends planes to spray herbicides on suspected cocaine fields in colombia and opium poppy fields in afghanistan affiliated companies and partnersedit remotec a subsidiary is the foremost manufacturer of remote control vehicles for explosive ordnance disposal and hazardous material handling a ukbased subsidiary park air systems provides vhf and uhf groundtoair communications systems for the civil and defense markets northrop grumman has also worked closely with antenna associates inc a manufacturer of identification friend or foe iffsecondary surveillance radar ssr antennas located in massachusetts in august  northrop grumman acquired scaled composites in which it had previously owned a  stake in  northrop grumman began working with dhs systems llc manufacturer of the deployable rapid assembly shelter drash in new york as part of the us armys standard integrated command post system program historyedit originally formed in california in  by jack northrop the northrop corporation was reincorporated in delaware in  sedit in  northrop aircraft bought grumman aerospace famous for building the apollo lunar module to create northrop grumman ngcitation needed in  the new company acquired westinghouse electronic systems a major manufacturer of radar systemscitation needed and xetron corporation in  the defense computer contractor logicon was added which had acquired geodynamics corporation in march  and syscon corporation in february citation needed the assembly line for northrop p black widows at the northrop plant in hawthorne california in world war ii center wings and fuselages take shape on the left with more nearly finished complete ships on the right in  a merger between northrop grumman and competitor lockheed martin was considered but abandoned after resistance from the department of defense and department of justice that same year it acquired international research institute inc in  the company acquired teledyne ryan developer of surveillance systems and unma